parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of Takata airbags can cause serious injury or death in the event of a crash, as they may not deploy or may deploy incorrectly.
symptoms: Airbag warning light stays on
airbag does not deploy in a crash
airbag deploys incorrectly
passenger side airbag sensor indicator illuminates on and off
airbag symbol comes on and off occasionally.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbag sensors can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to incorrect deployment or non-deployment of airbags in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Passenger side airbag sensor indicator illuminates on and off
airbag symbol comes on and off occasionally
airbag warning light stays on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of repair parts can cause delays in repairing recalled vehicles, leaving owners at risk of injury or death due to faulty airbags.
symptoms: Parts unavailable for repair
dealer unable to schedule appointment
manufacturer exceeds reasonable time for recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door lock actuator can cause the doors to lock or unlock unexpectedly, making it difficult or impossible to enter or exit the vehicle, which can lead to safety issues, especially in emergency situations.
symptoms: The doors lock or unlock on their own
the doors make a loud noise or buzzing sound when locking or unlocking
the doors do not stay locked or unlocked
the door lock actuator fails to respond to the key fob or manual locking/unlocking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door lock actuator can cause the doors to unlock or lock unexpectedly, which can lead to safety risks, such as children or unauthorized individuals gaining access to the vehicle, or accidents caused by doors opening while the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: The doors unlock or lock unexpectedly
the doors do not stay locked
the doors make a loud clanking or grinding noise
the doors will not unlock or lock manually or automatically
the doors unlock or lock independently while driving.
